    "minides": "Germany's finest open-top GT — 374 hp B58 inline-six, 48V mild hybrid, xDrive AWD, M Sport exhaust, fabric roof in 18 seconds. India's only 6-cylinder convertible under ₹1.5 crore.",
    "description": "Launched in India on 4 May 2026 at ₹1.09 crore (ex-showroom), the BMW M440i xDrive Convertible (G23) is BMW India's sole convertible offering following the Z4's global discontinuation. It is sold as a fully-loaded single variant CBU. Power comes from the B58 3.0L inline-six TwinPower Turbo producing 374 hp and 500 Nm, backed by a 48V mild-hybrid integrated starter generator, paired with an 8-speed Steptronic Sport automatic and xDrive AWD. The fabric soft-top opens or closes in 18 seconds at speeds up to 50 km/h. Key features include the BMW Curved Display (14.9-inch infotainment + 12.3-inch digital cluster), M Sport seats with electric memory and lumbar, a flat-bottom M leather steering wheel, Harman Kardon 12-speaker surround, head-up display, adaptive M Suspension, M Sport differential, M Shadowline exterior package, CSL-inspired woven laser-pattern tail lights, 19-inch bi-colour M double-spoke alloys, and wind deflectors behind the front seats. Rivals the Mercedes-Benz CLE Cabriolet (₹1.15 Cr) and AMG E 53 Cabriolet (₹1.30 Cr)."
  },
